reviews: I don't think companies like Hanes or others have a consistent suppliers. I previously purchased these exact same socks in the past (from a bricks and mortar store) and they were, and still are, very thick and durable. Not a hole in the heel yet, and that's saying something. So, when I needed some more, I ordered these and while they look the same, they are nowhere near the quality of the original ones. I can just tell from the thinness and coarseness of the material that they will not last. I would expect better consistency and if I order these Hanes socks today or next year, they should be the same.
product_name: Hanes Men's 6 pack FreshIQ Cushion Crew Sock

review_title: Why does Hanes sell so many different types of socks?
reviews:
I'm picky about socks, and when I find a pair that fits well and are comfortable, I like to stick to them.

After settling on Hanes and having them either wear out or get chewed by our puppy, I needed to buy some more pairs.

From what I remembered of the last time I bought socks, I bought Hanes crew cut FreshIQ socks, so i bought these since they matched up. However I immediately discovered that even though they had all the same labels and appearance, they were different and didn't feel as nice. Eventually I found the correct socks at Walmart, where they stocked Hanes Sport Cuts crew socks with FreshIQ which are more comfortable than these socks.

I wish Hanes didn't offer so many different variations of the same style of sock. At least now that I've found my preferred style, I can ensure I always get the right ones.
product_name: Hanes Men's 6 pack FreshIQ Cushion Crew Sock
